In bybit, go to https://www.bybit.com/data/basic/linear/contract-detail?symbol=SOLUSDT and then refer to open interest.
You can refer to open interest as an indicator as to which trading pair is traded more. It is basically the number of open contracts.
For example, if SOLUSDT has Open Interest of 1,293,762.70 and LTCUSDT has Open Interest of 298,634.30, it means SOLUSDT is more active
than LTCUSDT.

